You can insert a block with a custom width into the footer:

```typ
#set page(
  // needs center alignment, otherwise the block
  // will trail off the right edge of the page
  footer: context align(
    center,
    block(
      width: page.width - 2 * 5mm,
      // alignment is inherited, so you probably
      // want to reset it to left
      align(left)[
        This footer is wider than the text area.
      ]
    )
  )
)
```

I set up this example document to demonstrate:

```typst
#{
  set page(width: 10cm, height: 10cm)
  set page(margin: (x: 19mm, y: 19mm))
  set page(footer: {
    show: pad.with(x: -14mm)
    block(fill: green, width: 100%, height: 100%)[This is the footer]
  }, background: {
    set align(left + top)
    block(fill: white, width: 100%, height: 100%)[This is the background]
  })
  block(fill: yellow, width: 100%, height: 100%)[This is the main page area]
}
```

![Scratchpad(3)|500x500, 75%](upload://inpx6E9jmV3tVvNHtRgkjUbpijZ.png)

Drawing a little is useful to see what's going on. I used your desired margin of 19mm, but with a smaller page size just to make demonstration easier.

As you can see we can add negative padding to the footer, that should pull it out horizontally so that effectively there's only 5 mm x-margin left for the footer while rest of the page uses the configured 19mm margin.

Hello. If the footer must be wider than the page body, then you will have to use something like [`pad`](https://typst.app/docs/reference/layout/pad/) inside the [`page.footer`](https://typst.app/docs/reference/layout/page/#parameters-footer).

```typ
#set page(margin: (x: 19mm, y: 2cm), footer: context {
  pad(x: -page.margin.left + 5mm, counter(page).display())
})
```

Here is a visual example:

```typ
#set page(margin: (x: 19mm, y: 2cm))
#set page(footer: context {
  let page-number = counter(page).display()
  let margin = 5mm
  // pad(x: -page.margin.left + margin, rect(width: 100%, height: 100%))
  // pad(x: -page.margin.left + margin, page-number)
  pad(x: -page.margin.left + margin, {
    block(width: 100%, height: 100%, stroke: 1pt, page-number)
  })
})
#set page(background: rect(width: 100%, height: 100%))
#place(rect(width: 100%, height: 100%))
#lorem(100)
```

